
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lwp-dump` baraye didan va tahlil kardane etela'ate HTTP az yek URL estefade mishavad. In dastoor mitavanad header-ha, content, va digar etela'ate marboot be request va response-haye HTTP ra neshan dahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lwp-dump -d`  --> 🐞 Debug mode ra fa'al mikonad, va etela'ate bishtari dar morede process neshan midahad.
    🔹 `lwp-dump -v`  --> 📢 Verbose mode ra fa'al mikonad, va detail-haye bishtari ra neshan midahad.
    🔹 `lwp-dump -h`  --> ℹ️ Header-haye HTTP ra faghat neshan midahad va content-ha ra skip mikonad.
    🔹 `lwp-dump -t <timeout>` --> ⏳ Zamane timeout baraye request ra moshakhas mikonad (be saniye).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ lwp-dump http://www.example.com

    🔹 Namayesh hameye etela'ate HTTP (header va content) az website example.com.

    $ lwp-dump -h http://www.example.com

    🔹 Faghat header-haye HTTP az website example.com ra neshan midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ lwp-dump -d http://www.example.com

    🔹 Debug mode ra fa'al mikonad va etela'ate bishtari ra dar morede process namayesh midahad, ke baraye troubleshoot kardan mofid ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lwp-dump` command is used to view and analyze HTTP information from a URL. This command can display headers, content, and other information related to HTTP requests and responses.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lwp-dump -d`  --> 🐞 Enables debug mode, showing more information about the process.
    🔹 `lwp-dump -v`  --> 📢 Enables verbose mode, showing more details.
    🔹 `lwp-dump -h`  --> ℹ️ Shows only the HTTP headers and skips the content.
    🔹 `lwp-dump -t <timeout>` --> ⏳ Specifies the timeout for the request (in seconds).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ lwp-dump http://www.example.com

    🔹 Displays all HTTP information (headers and content) from the website example.com.

    $ lwp-dump -h http://www.example.com

    🔹 Shows only the HTTP headers from the website example.com.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ lwp-dump -d http://www.example.com

    🔹 Enables debug mode and displays more information about the process, which is useful for troubleshooting.

